# Browser Test Verification Report

## Obligation

After completing **any browser-based visual verification** (per the web-testing-methodology rule or user request), you MUST produce a verification report with screenshots, email it, and send an SMS.

This is a **mandatory post-verification step**. Do NOT skip it. Do NOT claim verification is complete until this report has been sent.

## Preferred Method: GrabScreenShot Tool

Use the standardized `C:\opt\src\GrabScreenShot` project:

```powershell
# Capture all apps, send email + SMS (one command)
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\GrabScreenShot\Invoke-GrabScreenShot.ps1"

# Capture a single app, no notifications
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\GrabScreenShot\Invoke-GrabScreenShot.ps1" -AppName DocView -NoEmail -NoSms

# Capture from test server
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\GrabScreenShot\Invoke-GrabScreenShot.ps1" -BaseUrl http://t-no1fkxtst-app
```

The tool handles screenshots, report generation, email, and SMS automatically. Configure apps in `C:\opt\src\GrabScreenShot\apps.json`.

## Manual Fallback: Step-by-Step

If the GrabScreenShot tool is unavailable, follow these manual steps.

### Step 1: Capture Screenshots

For every page verified during browser testing:

1. Navigate to the page in the browser (using `browser_navigate` or Puppeteer)
2. If the page supports dark mode, activate it before capturing
3. Save a **full-page screenshot** as PNG to a temporary folder (e.g., `C:\temp\screenshots\`)
4. Use a descriptive filename: `{AppName}-{PageName}.png` (e.g., `ServerMonitorDashboard-index.png`)

## Step 2: Build the Verification Report

Compose a report that includes for **every page tested**:

| Field | Content |
|-------|---------|
| **App name** | Human-readable name (e.g., "Server Monitor Dashboard") |
| **Full URL** | The exact URL used to access the page in the browser, in plain text |
| **Status** | PASS or FAIL with brief reason |
| **Screenshot** | Attached PNG file |

### Report format (email body)

```
FkAuth Browser Verification Report
Date: {date/time}
Environment: {server or localhost}

Apps Tested:
 1. FkAuth Login — http://localhost/FkAuth/login.html — PASS
 2. FkAuth Admin — http://localhost/FkAuth/admin.html — PASS
 3. DocView — http://localhost/DocView/ — PASS
 4. GenericLogHandler — http://localhost/GenericLogHandler/ — PASS
 5. ServerMonitorDashboard — http://localhost/ServerMonitorDashboard/ — PASS
 6. AutoDocJson — http://localhost/AutoDocJson/ — PASS

Verification Details:
 - Tenant CSS injection: {working/not working}
 - User menu: {visible/not visible}
 - Auth flow: {code exchange / token / cookie}
 - Dark mode: {activated/not available}

Screenshots attached: {count} PNG files
```

## Step 3: Send Email

Send the report and screenshots via email:

```powershell
$emailParams = @{
    To          = "geir.helge.starholm@felleskjopet.no"
    From        = "fkauth-agent@felleskjopet.no"
    Subject     = "FkAuth Browser Test Report - $(Get-Date -Format 'yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm')"
    Body        = $reportBody
    SmtpServer  = "smtp.fknett.fk.no"
    Attachments = $screenshotFiles
}
Send-MailMessage @emailParams
```

If `smtp.fknett.fk.no` is unreachable from the current machine, try the GlobalFunctions module:

```powershell
Import-Module GlobalFunctions -Force
Send-Email -To "geir.helge.starholm@felleskjopet.no" -Subject $subject -Body $reportBody -Attachments $screenshotFiles
```

If both fail, fall back to `Send-MailMessage` with port 25 and a 10-second timeout test first:

```powershell
$tcp = New-Object System.Net.Sockets.TcpClient
if ($tcp.ConnectAsync("smtp.fknett.fk.no", 25).Wait(10000)) {
    $tcp.Close()
    Send-MailMessage @emailParams
} else {
    Write-Host "SMTP unreachable, saving report to file instead"
    $reportBody | Out-File "C:\temp\screenshots\REPORT.txt"
}
```

## Step 4: Send SMS

After the email is sent (or attempted), send an SMS summary:

```powershell
$smsNumber = switch ($env:USERNAME) {
    "FKGEISTA" { "+4797188358" }
    "FKSVEERI" { "+4795762742" }
    "FKMISTA"  { "+4799348397" }
    "FKCELERI" { "+4745269945" }
    default    { "+4797188358" }
}

Import-Module GlobalFunctions -Force
Send-Sms -Receiver $smsNumber -Message "Browser test done. {N} apps verified. {pass/fail}. Email sent."
```

SMS must be under 160 characters. Include: number of apps tested, overall pass/fail, whether email was sent.

## When This Applies

- After **any** visual browser verification task
- After deploying changes and running the full verification flow
- When the user explicitly asks to "test and report" or "verify and send screenshots"
- After running Build-And-Publish + IIS-RedeployAll and verifying the result

## Mandatory Ordering After Deploy

The correct sequence after a code change is:

1. `Build-And-Publish-ALL.ps1` (or `Build-And-Publish.ps1` for single project)
2. `IIS-RedeployAll.ps1` (installs from staging to IIS, recycles app pools)
3. **GrabScreenShot** (captures screenshots, emails report, sends SMS)

**NEVER send SMS claiming "all OK" before step 3 completes with ALL PASS.**

```powershell
# Full sequence
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File ".\Build-And-Publish-ALL.ps1"
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\FKMenyPSH\DevTools\WebSites\IIS-DeployApp\IIS-RedeployAll.ps1"
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\GrabScreenShot\Invoke-GrabScreenShot.ps1"
```

## Important Notes

- Always include the **full URL in plain text** in the email body (not just app names)
- Screenshots must be **actual browser captures**, not API response screenshots
- If a page FAILS, still include it in the report with the failure reason and screenshot
- The email recipient is always `geir.helge.starholm@felleskjopet.no` unless the user specifies otherwise
- **Do NOT send SMS before email with screenshots is sent**
- **Do NOT claim success based on API checks alone -- visual verification is mandatory**
